This paper deals with the problem of estimating high moments of a data stream, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. The problem is related to data stream algorithms, which is a subfield of computer science dealing with processing and analyzing data in a streaming fashion. The paper presents a lower bound for the problem, which is a theoretical result in the area of computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
